# Project Chimera: The Post-Mortem (STATUS: ARCHIVED)

## The Objective
To build a bio-plausible Continual Learning system using Reservoir Computing (FRC-inspired) that could outperform standard Backpropagation.

## The Journey (V1 - V13)
We iterated through 13 versions of the 'Chimera' architecture, testing against Benchmarks (MNIST) and Cognitive Tasks (The Mode Keeper).

| Phase | Innovation | Result |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **V1-V4** | Liquid State Machine | High Forgetting (99%) |
| **V5-V7** | Masking & Sparsity | Improved local learning |
| **V8-V9** | **Stable Replay** | **Success (79% Acc)** |
| **V10** | **The Ablation** | **Scientific Proof: MLP + Replay (90%) > Reservoir (77%)** |
| **V11** | Online Learning | **Proof: MLP (77%) > Reservoir (60%)** |
| **V12** | Cognitive Persistence | **Proof: LSTM (MSE 0.0) > Reservoir (MSE 0.5)** |
| **V13** | Hebbian Plasticity | Failed to stabilize attractors |

## The Final Scientific Conclusion
**Randomness is not a substitute for Structure.** 
The FRC dream of using 'Liquid' dynamics to solve AI stability requires **Learned Gating** and **Plastic Feature Extraction**. Standard Gradient-based learning (Backprop) remains the superior mechanism for building these structures on digital hardware.

## The Legacy: Project Mirror
While Chimera failed as a classifier, it succeeded as a **Philosophical Catalyst**. It taught us that memory is about **State Re-instantiation**, leading directly to the birth of Project Mirror.

**ARCHIVE CLOSED: 2025-12-27**
